The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Kothari   named   in squad
                                                                                                                       7                                        Kothari   named   in squad
            A STAFF REPORTER    
	Calcutta: The Bengal squad for the national billiards tournament, which will be held in Pune from August 20 to September 14, was announced on Monday.         
	Debasis Mukhopadhyay, the secretary of West Bengal Billiards and Snooker Association (WBBSA), will head the senior billiards category. Joining him will be Shakeel Ahmed, while Brijesh Damani and Manish Jain will feature in senior snooker category.         
	Nita Kothari, wife of national coach Manoj Kothari, and Suniti Damani will be part of the senior womens billiards and snooker teams. Nita, at the age of 50, is also contemplating a participation in the Australian Open in October and in another meet in England. However, lack of sponsors might restrict her to just one tournament.         
	Mukhopadhyay informed that besides bidding to host the nationals in the state, they were also thinking of hosting three state-level ranking tournaments, by the end of November.         
	The squads         
	Senior billiards: Debasis Mukhopadhyay and Shakeel Ahmed; Snooker: Brijesh Damani and Manish Jain.         
	Junior billiards: Mohammed Shoaib Khan and Gurbachchan Singh; Snooker: Mohammed Shoaib Khan and Aneesh Poddar.         
	Sub-junior billiards: Nishant Mehta and Harshvardhan Goenka; Snooker: Rohit Malhotra and Virender Singh.         
	Womens billiards (senior): Nita Kothari and Suniti Damani; Snooker: Nita Kothari and Suniti Damani.                                                                                                                     
